.TH "rdma_move_grh_sgid_attr" 9 "rdma_move_grh_sgid_attr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rdma_move_grh_sgid_attr \- Sets the sgid attribute of GRH, taking ownership of the reference
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rdma_move_grh_sgid_attr
.BI "(struct rdma_ah_attr *attr "  ","
.BI "union ib_gid *dgid "  ","
.BI "u32 flow_label "  ","
.BI "u8 hop_limit "  ","
.BI "u8 traffic_class "  ","
.BI "const struct ib_gid_attr *sgid_attr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "attr" 12
Pointer to AH attribute structure
.IP "dgid" 12
Destination GID
.IP "flow_label" 12
Flow label
.IP "hop_limit" 12
Hop limit
.IP "traffic_class" 12
traffic class
.IP "sgid_attr" 12
Pointer to SGID attribute
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This takes ownership of the sgid_attr reference. The caller must ensure
\fBrdma_destroy_ah_attr\fP is called before destroying the rdma_ah_attr after
calling this function.
